Sentencas: This work focuses on the role of CO and CO2 usually present in syngas generated by biomass gasification when they are flowed in a Ni-YSZ-based SOPC.
Titulo: Effects of carbon monoxide, carbon dioxide, and methane on nickel/yttria-stabilized zirconia-based solid oxide fuel cells performance for direct coupling with a gasifier

Sentencas: Polarization, power versus intensity and electrochemical impedance spectroscopy measurements are performed and the theoretical aspect is enhanced with comparison with values of the Nernst potentials of the two H2O/H-2 and CO2/CO couples.
Titulo: Effects of carbon monoxide, carbon dioxide, and methane on nickel/yttria-stabilized zirconia-based solid oxide fuel cells performance for direct coupling with a gasifier

Sentencas: The CO as electrochemical reactant is clearly highlighted, and also compared to H2.
Titulo: Effects of carbon monoxide, carbon dioxide, and methane on nickel/yttria-stabilized zirconia-based solid oxide fuel cells performance for direct coupling with a gasifier

Sentencas: Indeed, power density values of 460 mW cm(-2) and 540 mW cm(-2) are obtained at 750 C when the cell is fueled with a 50% CO-50% N-2 mixture and a 50% H-2-50% N-2 mixture respectively, and the use of CO leads to higher power density values when the percentage of the fuel in the Fuel/N-2 mixture is lower than 27%, the use of higher amounts of CO inducing a large increase of the total resistance of the cell.
Titulo: Effects of carbon monoxide, carbon dioxide, and methane on nickel/yttria-stabilized zirconia-based solid oxide fuel cells performance for direct coupling with a gasifier

Sentencas: The impact on the efficiency of the cell of the presence of CH4 is also examined using electrochemical measurements.
Titulo: Effects of carbon monoxide, carbon dioxide, and methane on nickel/yttria-stabilized zirconia-based solid oxide fuel cells performance for direct coupling with a gasifier

Sentencas: Finally, power density values of 502 mW cm(-2) is obtained at 750 degrees C when the cell is fueled with a 50% N2-20% CO-17% H-2-10% CO2-3% CH4 mixture which appears to a be a realistic composition corresponding to the exhaust of the gasifier.
Titulo: Effects of carbon monoxide, carbon dioxide, and methane on nickel/yttria-stabilized zirconia-based solid oxide fuel cells performance for direct coupling with a gasifier
